{
  "genre": "lofi",
  "mode": "focus",
  "mixStrategy": "FREQUENCY SEPARATION: Bass (Electric Bass, GM 33) owns 20-300Hz with MIDI 36-48, providing the harmonic foundation with root notes. Chords (Warm Pad, GM 89) fill 300Hz-2kHz with MIDI 48-67 playing sustained 7th voicings. Melody (Electric Piano/Rhodes, GM 4) sits at 1-8kHz with MIDI 60-79 playing gentle jazzy phrases. Drums (GM 0 channel 10) provide rhythmic backbone across the spectrum with soft boom-bap patterns.\n\nHARMONIC PLAN (Key of C, Dorian inflections, 45 seconds): The chord progression cycles through two 8-bar phrases at 75 BPM (0.8s per beat, 3.2s per bar). Phrase A: Dm7 (ii7) for 2 bars \u2192 G7 (V7) for 2 bars \u2192 Cmaj7 (Imaj7) for 2 bars \u2192 Cmaj7 for 2 bars. Phrase B: Cmaj7 (Imaj7) for 1 bar \u2192 Am7 (vi7) for 1 bar \u2192 Dm7 (ii7) for 2 bars \u2192 G7 (V7) for 2 bars \u2192 Cmaj7 for ~1.5 bars. All tracks change chords TOGETHER on the same beat.\n\nRHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Drums provide the grid \u2014 kick on beats 1 and 2.5 (the \"and\" of 2), snare on 2 and 4, hi-hats on 8th notes with ghost notes. Bass locks with the kick drum, playing roots on beat 1 and walking notes approaching the next chord. Melody breathes BETWEEN drum hits, entering on off-beats and using space. Chords sustain underneath everything, changing smoothly at chord boundaries.\n\nENERGY ARC (6 segments of ~7.5s each): Seg1 (0-7.5s) energy 0.4 \u2014 drums + bass enter softly, sparse melody hints. Seg2 (7.5-15s) energy 0.6 \u2014 melody enters with phrases, chords fill in. Seg3 (15-22.5s) energy 0.7 \u2014 full arrangement, melody most active. Seg4 (22.5-30s) energy 0.7 \u2014 sustained peak, slight variation. Seg5 (30-37.5s) energy 0.7 \u2014 maintained density. Seg6 (37.5-45s) energy 0.5 \u2014 gentle pullback, melody thins, drums soften.\n\nLO-FI FEEL: All velocities kept soft (40-70 range). Notes placed slightly behind the grid for relaxed swing feel. Melody uses 7ths, 9ths, and pentatonic shapes. Bass is simple and repetitive. Chords are warm sustained pads. Everything is intimate and habituating for focus.",
